$ cpan

`cpan` is a command line tool to easily interact with → development/languages/Perl/CPAN, currently using the → development/languages/Perl/modules[Perl module]
→ development/languages/Perl/modules/CPAN[CPAN.pm].

{ Installing a perl module #cpan-install-perl-module

code {
$ cpan → development/languages/Perl/modules/DBD/Oracle[DBD::Oracle]
code }

~Forcing an installation~
-
If the test suite does not run without errors, `cpan` won't by default install the module. In order to still install such a module, the `-f` flag can be used:
code {
cpan -f → development/languages/Perl/modules/Crypt/Random[Crypt::Random]
code }

}

sa:

  `cpan -V` and → development/languages/Perl/installation/directory[Perl installation directories]
